So,%0a%3c you'll want enough fighters to kill what an attacker might bring to kill%0a%3c your Cruisers.  Calculate which of these units is most efficient against%0a%3c your Cruisers, and then calculate the Fighters necessary. The Death Star%0a%3c is at least nice enough to carry many of the FTs you'll need.%0a%3c %0a%3c So, your Death Star Support Fleet would include: Cruisers and Fighters;%0a%3c the quintessence of the [[Small Fleet Doctrine]]. Think of this as either defense-in-depth or Small Fleet defense.%0a%3c %0a%3c Capital Strength in Numbers%0a%3c ---------------------------%0a%3c %0a%3c The second approach is to create a Stack, which provides strength in numbers.%0a%3c Simply put, create a stack of a capital unit: Titans, Levis, Dreads or Death%0a%3c Stars. Yes, these are vulnerable to Battleships (or Heavy Cruisers) as%0a%3c appropriate. But, their large numbers make it more difficult to bring enough of%0a%3c an attacking fleet to bear.%0a%3c %0a%3c Harvest the Derbs%0a%3c -----------------%0a%3c %0a%3c Finally, have enough Recyclers ''nearby'' to harvest ''all'' the derbs.  Keep%0a%3c the Recyclers away from your fleet as they provide no value in defense but%0a%3c benefit your attacker.  Assume your DS and its support fleet is destroyed. You%0a%3c will want _at least_ one Recycler for every five credits of your fleet's value.%0a%3c This will allow harvesting%0a%3c %0a%3c (:comment This page has been edited using Pywe:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a---%0a> %0a> What to use the DS for? It's been called a credit piggy bank; or a piata. The URL at the bottom shows the armour cost efficiency. DS has a .11 efficiency. Any unit with a higher value is more efficient (once Derbs are harvested) But, all is not lost.%0a> %0a> Know what it takes to kill a DS by unit type. Run the numbers and keep note of them. Treat a DS like an LV short-stack: good for crunching fleets with units less than BB in size; or with an insufficient number of BBs. If we could catch a fleet in a retreat trap, then you could crunch it.%0a> %0a> [color='yellowHow to protect the DS? Keep it in the air, or at least away from threats. Build a support fleet that is efficient against BBs. Have enough fleet on hand to kill all the BBs required to kill the DS; that will prevent the BBs from being efficient against your DS. This means you'll want a lot of CRs. As FR, CV, DD are efficient against CRs, you'll need to calculate the amount of fleet necessary to kill the CRs protecting the DS.%0a> %0a> http://espacesociety.org/AstroEmpires/NewFighterRuleAnalysis%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
